#: ../../source/about/contribute/review/index.rst:4
msgid ""
"The maintainers and working group leads of the Istio Docs Working Group "
"(WG) approve all changes to the `Istio website </docs/>`_."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/about/contribute/review/index.rst:7
msgid ""
"A **documentation reviewer** is a trusted contributor that approves "
"content that meets the acceptance criteria described in the `review "
"criteria <#review-criteria>`_. All content reviews follow the process "
"described in `Reviewing content PRs <#review-content-prs>`_."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/about/contribute/review/index.rst:12
msgid ""
"Only Docs Maintainers and WG Leads can merge content into the `istio.io "
"repository <https://github.com/istio/istio.io>`_."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/about/contribute/review/index.rst:15
msgid ""
"Content for Istio often needs to be reviewed on short notice and not all "
"content has the same relevance. The last minute nature of contributions "
"and the finite number of reviewers make the prioritization of content "
"reviews necessary to function at scale. This page provides clear review "
"criteria to ensure all review work happens **consistently**, **reliably**"
" and follows the **same quality standards**."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/about/contribute/review/index.rst:23
msgid "Review content PRs"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/about/contribute/review/index.rst:25
msgid ""
"Documentation reviewers, maintainers, and WG leads follow a clear process"
" to review content PRs to ensure all reviews are consistent. The process "
"is as follows:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/about/contribute/review/index.rst:29
msgid "The **Contributor** submits a new content PR to the istio.io repository."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/about/contribute/review/index.rst:31
msgid ""
"The **Reviewer** performs a review of the content and determines if it "
"meets the acceptance criteria."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/about/contribute/review/index.rst:33
msgid ""
"The **Reviewer** adds any technical WG pertinent for the content if the "
"contributor hasn’t already."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/about/contribute/review/index.rst:35
msgid ""
"The **Contributor** and the **Reviewer** work together until the content "
"meets all required acceptance criteria and the issues are addressed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/about/contribute/review/index.rst:38
msgid ""
"If the content is urgent and meeting the supplemental acceptance criteria"
" requires significant effort, the **Reviewer** files a follow up issue on"
" the istio.io repository to address the problems at a later date."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/about/contribute/review/index.rst:42
msgid ""
"The **Contributor** addresses all required and supplemental feedback as "
"agreed by the Reviewer and Contributor. Any feedback filed in the follow "
"up issues is addressed later."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/about/contribute/review/index.rst:45
msgid ""
"When a **technical** WG lead or maintainer approves the content PR, the "
"**Reviewer** can approve the PR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/about/contribute/review/index.rst:47
msgid ""
"If a Docs WG maintainer or lead reviewed the content, they not only "
"approve, but they also merge the content. Otherwise, maintainers and "
"leads are automatically notified of the **Reviewer’s** approval and "
"prioritize approving and merging the already reviewed content."
msgstr ""

